Author:
(Sherry) Shanshan Ruan 260471837 Enters a valid but random bid. Passes a configurable number of times. If the robot does not pass, it uses a universal probability distribution across all bids permitted.

public RandomBiddingStrategy(int pPassFrequency)
Builds a robot that passes the specified percentage number of the time.

Parameters:
pPassFrequency - A percentage point (e.g., 50 for 50%) of the time the robot will pass. Must be between 0 and 100 inclusive. Whether the robot passes is determined at random.

Produces a valid bid, i.e., a between 6 and 10 for any suit or no trump, that is higher that the last bid.

Specified by:
selectBid in interface IBiddingStrategy
